---
import Base from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import EmailCTA from '../../components/EmailCTA.astro';
import { solutions } from '../../data/solutions';
const schema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'CollectionPage',
  name: 'Transformer Temperature Monitoring Solutions',
  description: 'Problem-led transformer temperature monitoring solutions for OTI, WTI, cooling control, remote monitoring and retrofit selection.',
  mainEntity: { '@type': 'ItemList', itemListElement: solutions.map((item, index) => ({ '@type': 'ListItem', position: index + 1, name: item.title, url: `https://ankaili.com${item.href}` })) }
};
---
<Base title="Transformer Temperature Monitoring Solutions | INNO" description="Select transformer temperature monitoring solutions for OTI, WTI, BWY and BWR controllers, cooling control, remote monitoring and retrofit projects." schema={schema}>
  <section class="page-hero"><div class="container"><p class="eyebrow">Solutions for oil-immersed transformers</p><h1>Transformer Temperature Monitoring Solutions</h1><p>Measure top-oil or winding temperature, control cooling equipment, send data to your control system or replace an existing BWY or BWR controller.</p></div></section>
  <section class="section"><div class="container"><div class="answer-block">Start with the job the instrument must perform. INNO can help you compare local indicators, cooling and alarm contacts, Pt100 or 4-20 mA outputs, RS485 monitoring and replacement options.</div><div class="section-head"><h2>What Do You Need to Monitor or Control?</h2><p class="lead">Choose the closest requirement to see suitable product families and the information needed for selection.</p></div><div class="solution-grid">{solutions.map((item, index) => <article class="solution-card"><a class="solution-card-media" href={item.href} aria-label={`View ${item.title}`}><img src={item.image} alt={`${item.title} application environment`} width="1600" height="900" loading={index < 2 ? 'eager' : 'lazy'}></a><div class="solution-card-body"><p>{item.focus}</p><h2><a href={item.href}>{item.title}</a></h2><p>{item.description}</p></div></article>)}</div></div></section>
  <section class="section tint"><article class="container prose"><h2>How to Choose the Right Product</h2><p>An oil temperature indicator measures top oil at the thermometer pocket. A winding temperature indicator adds a load-current-related thermal rise to show simulated winding temperature.</p><h3>Decide what should happen when temperature rises</h3><p>The controller may start fans or pumps, trigger an alarm, provide a trip input or send a temperature value to a PLC, RTU, SCADA system or remote display. List each required action before choosing the number of contacts and signal output.</p><h3>Match the product to the transformer</h3><p>Send the full model, range, contact functions, output, power supply, capillary, sensing bulb, thread and mounting details. A complete model code is especially important for BWY and BWR replacements.</p></article></section>
  <EmailCTA title="Request a Solution Recommendation and Quote" subject="Transformer temperature monitoring solution review" />
</Base>
